            "content": "[link:/services/toilet-installation|Toilet Services] - We install and repair all toilet types for Green Valley homes: high-efficiency toilets using 1.28 gallons per flush versus old 3.5-5.0 GPF models (saving $50-90 annually for 2-person household), comfort-height toilets (ADA-compliant with easier sit/stand for seniors), dual-flush toilets with separate buttons for liquid (0.8 GPF) and solid waste (1.6 GPF), pressure-assisted toilets for superior flushing power, smart toilets with bidet functions, and basic toilet repairs (fill valves, flappers, wax rings, tank bolts). Common Green Valley toilet issues include wax ring failures from shifting foundations on expansive soils, fill valve problems from hard water mineral buildup, flapper deterioration from chlorinated water, and weak flushing from clogged rim jets (hard water deposits). Typical costs: $450-750 for standard toilet installation, $650-1,200 for comfort-height or dual-flush upgrades, $120-280 for professional repairs. Water-saving ROI: Replacing one old 3.5 GPF toilet saves 12,000-14,000 gallons annually (2-person household), reducing water bills $45-65/year and paying for new efficient toilet in 7-10 years."
