            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Phase 2: Scheduling & Preparation (Days 8-21): Once you've decided to proceed, proper planning ensures minimal disruption to your Green Valley lifestyle. Scheduling considerations: Most Green Valley homeowners prefer avoiding winter visitor season (December-March) when family guests visit, selecting slower seasons (late spring or early fall) for contractor availability, allowing 2-3 weeks lead time for project scheduling and permitting, and coordinating around travel plans ensuring you're home for key project phases. Pre-project preparation: Clear access to attic spaces and crawl spaces where new piping will run, protect or remove valuable items from areas where drywall access needed, arrange temporary relocation if water will be off overnight (though we maintain evening water availability for basic needs), notify neighbors about temporary noise and contractor vehicles, and secure pets in safe areas away from work zones. Permitting: We handle all permit applications and inspections—typically takes 5-7 business days for approval. Material selection: Choose between PEX (economical, excellent performance, $6,500-10,500 typical Green Valley homes) or copper (premium traditional choice, superior longevity, $9,500-15,000 typical homes). Most Green Valley retirees choose PEX for excellent value and performance."
